Thick, waves of crude washed Saturday from South Korea's largest ever oil spill, turning seagulls black and threatening fish farms along a 17-kilometer (11-mile) stretch of scenic and rich coastline.
Thousands of South Korean troops and volunteers Sunday are cleaning up crude oil gushed into the sea.
A crane - carrying vessel slammed into a Hong Kong - registered oil tanker in seas off South Korea's west coast Friday causing tanker to leak 110,000 barrels of crude oil ,.
About 10.5 million liters of crude oil leaked to waters off the western coast of South Korea.
